To create a custom Python composition with a given set of libraries, you define a Nix expression within a `.nix` file. This expression typically imports `<nixpkgs>` and uses the `python.withPackages` function to wrap Python, ensuring the specified libraries are available. A common template for this is:
```nix
with import <nixpkgs> { };
python.withPackages (packages:
  with packages; [
    ... list of python packages ...
  ]
)
```
This enables you to create a `python` command that can access the defined set of Python packages.
